/*
:name: latch_attr_drop
:type: error
:tolg: 1
:error: SILENTLY DROPPED
*/
// todo/livehd/2f-latch M0 fail-closed test.
//
// The Latch cell is a 3-pin skeleton (din / enable / posclk — graph/cell.cpp),
// and tolg's finalize_regs latch branch `continue`s BEFORE the clock / posclk /
// reset / initial wiring that flops get. So every one of those attributes used
// to be SILENTLY DISCARDED: this exact declaration compiled exit 0 with zero
// warnings and emitted Verilog byte-identical to a plain transparent-high latch
// — the author's `clock_pin`, `posclk` and `init` simply evaporated.
//
// An attribute that vanishes without a word is worse than one that is not
// supported, so tolg now REFUSES. The error is lifted attribute by attribute as
// M2 adds the corresponding pins to the cell.
//
// Guarded shapes (any one of these alone must error): clock_pin, posclk,
// init/initial, reset_pin, sync/async, negreset. NOTE `init=nil` is NOT an
// error — "nil" is the explicit NO-reset marker the slang reader stamps on
// every latch declare, so nothing is being dropped there (that exemption is
// what keeps the six live latch equiv goldens compiling).
pub mod ldrop(en:bool, d:u8, ck2:bool) -> (q:u8@[0]) {
  reg l:u8:[latch=true, clock_pin=ck2, posclk=false, init=3]
  if en {
    l = d
  }
  q = l
}
